title: Watch: High School Runner Pulled Over By Cop Who Surprises Him With Trophy
text:
Meanwhile, Brie Oakley was in statistics class at Grandview High School in Aurora, Colorado, when Molly Huddle , two-time Olympian, barged in with the award, saying that the senior had a “100 percent” probability of winning the Gatorade National Girls Cross Country Runner of the Year award. Oakley also won Nike Cross Nationals in 2016. 
Related: From the Soccer Field to National Champion in 18 Months 
The award is based not only on performance, but on academic records. Clinger maintains a 4.0 GPA and is headed to Brigham Young University in the fall. Oakley maintains a 4.60 GPA and will attend the University of California at Berkeley after graduation.
